{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:sirach.43",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 43,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 43 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:1",
      "text": "The pride of the height, the clear firmament, the beauty of heaven, with his glorious shew;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:2",
      "text": "The sun when it appeareth, declaring at his rising a marvellous instrument, the work of the most High:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:3",
      "text": "At noon it parcheth the country, and who can abide the burning heat thereof?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:4",
      "text": "A man blowing a furnace is in works of heat, but the sun burneth the mountains three times more; breathing out fiery vapours, and sending forth bright beams, it dimmeth the eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:5",
      "text": "Great is the Lord that made it; and at his commandment runneth hastily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:6",
      "text": "He made the moon also to serve in her season for a declaration of times, and a sign of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:7",
      "text": "From the moon is the sign of feasts, a light that decreaseth in her perfection.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:8",
      "text": "The month is called after her name, increasing wonderfully in her changing, being an instrument of the armies above, shining in the firmament of heaven;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:9",
      "text": "The beauty of heaven, the glory of the stars, an ornament giving light in the highest places of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:10",
      "text": "At the commandment of the Holy One they will stand in their order, and never faint in their watches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:11",
      "text": "Look upon the rainbow, and praise him that made it; very beautiful it is in the brightness thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:12",
      "text": "It compasseth the heaven about with a glorious circle, and the hands of the most High have bended it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:13",
      "text": "By his commandment he maketh the snow to fall aplace, and sendeth swiftly the lightnings of his judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:14",
      "text": "Through this the treasures are opened: and clouds fly forth as fowls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:15",
      "text": "By his great power he maketh the clouds firm, and the hailstones are broken small.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:16",
      "text": "At his sight the mountains are shaken, and at his will the south wind bloweth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:17",
      "text": "The noise of the thunder maketh the earth to tremble: so doth the northern storm and the whirlwind: as birds flying he scattereth the snow, and the falling down thereof is as the lighting of grasshoppers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:18",
      "text": "The eye marvelleth at the beauty of the whiteness thereof, and the heart is astonished at the raining of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:19",
      "text": "The hoarfrost also as salt he poureth on the earth, and being congealed, it lieth on the top of sharp stakes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:20",
      "text": "When the cold north wind bloweth, and the water is congealed into ice, it abideth upon every gathering together of water, and clotheth the water as with a breastplate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:21",
      "text": "It devoureth the mountains, and burneth the wilderness, and consumeth the grass as fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:22",
      "text": "A present remedy of all is a mist coming speedily, a dew coming after heat refresheth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:23",
      "text": "By his counsel he appeaseth the deep, and planteth islands therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:24",
      "text": "They that sail on the sea tell of the danger thereof; and when we hear it with our ears, we marvel thereat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:25",
      "text": "For therein be strange and wondrous works, variety of all kinds of beasts and whales created.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:26",
      "text": "By him the end of them hath prosperous success, and by his word all things consist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:27",
      "text": "We may speak much, and yet come short: wherefore in sum, he is all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:28",
      "text": "How shall we be able to magnify him? for he is great above all his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:29",
      "text": "The Lord is terrible and very great, and marvellous is his power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:30",
      "text": "When ye glorify the Lord, exalt him as much as ye can; for even yet will he far exceed: and when ye exalt him, put forth all your strength, and be not weary; for ye can never go far enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:31",
      "text": "Who hath seen him, that he might tell us? and who can magnify him as he is?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:32",
      "text": "There are yet hid greater things than these be, for we have seen but a few of his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.43.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 43,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 43:33",
      "text": "For the Lord hath made all things; and to the godly hath he given wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
